column5: Anyone ever buy groceries here? I'm thinking of picking up a few thing there on our way. Just curious on anyones thoughts about it. Mostly looking for French fries and ice cream. Let me know if you can. Thanks
They have a lot of different stuff, whether it is what you'll want is difficult to determine. Bill
there's a fairly large food store in grand marais and a huge one in two harbors phish
If Grand Portage doesn't have what you want/need, maybe Pigeon River will...
Hum... Might be a little bit of an old picture, but neat. Got a pic of the "Weeping Rock", where they smashed all the forbidden booze they found being brought over during Prohibition? Bill
I'll just take my chances. If they don't have it, I don't need it. I'm pretty sure they will though.
